{
  "doc_id": "58390",
  "text": "The effects of ivacaftor have also been studied in patients with severe impairment of lung function with an FEV 1 percent predicted to be ≤40 % ( Table 2 ) [CITATION_1] . Significant improvements in lung function, number of days of intravenous antibiotic therapy, weight and body mass index (BMI) were found among patients after treatment in a retrospective case-control study [CITATION_2] . In particular, reductions in treatment requirements -for example, number of inpatient days for intravenous antibiotics (median days per year reduced from 23 to 0, P = 0.001) -were felt to be clinically significant and greater than in studies involving patients with less severe lung disease [CITATION_3] .",
